OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FSome early brightness, but
OL,6,Fcloud thickening and wind
OL,7,Fstrengthening ahead of a band of
OL,8,Foccasionally heavy rain sweeping east
OL,9,Facross the region. Sunny spells and
OL,10,Fblustery showers in the afternoon,
OL,11,Fwith a risk of hail and thunder.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA mostly cloudy and breezy
OL,14,Fnight, with outbreaks of rain and
OL,15,Fshowers continuing through the evening
OL,16,Fand early hours. Mild.
OL,17,
OL,18,CThursday:FA mixture of sunny spells
OL,19,Fand blustery showers, these perhaps
OL,20,Fheavy and thundery at times. Windy.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
